<h2 id="cozy-zone"><a href="https://macstories.memberful.com/checkout?plan=138191" rel="noopener noreferrer">Cozy Zone</a></h2>
<div class="media-wrapper"><img decoding="async" src="https://cdn.macstories.net/untitled-19-1757255482122.png" alt=""><p class="image-caption"></p></div>
<p id="p14">We&rsquo;re equally excited to bring you <a href="https://macstories.memberful.com/checkout?plan=138191" rel="noopener noreferrer">Cozy Zone</a>, a members-only extension of Comfort Zone hosted by <a href="https://www.macstories.net/?author=52" rel="noopener noreferrer">Matt Birchler</a>, <a href="https://www.macstories.net/author/nileane/" rel="noopener noreferrer">Nil&eacute;ane</a>, and <a href="https://www.youtube.com/channel/UC8raOG7HXJoCUygx219fU4A" rel="noopener noreferrer">Chris Lawley</a>. It was a no-brainer to add Comfort Zone to MacStories, and the reaction from listeners has been beyond our expectations. It&rsquo;s the perfect blend of information and entertainment sprinkled with the hosts&rsquo; weird obsessions.</p>
<p id="p15">In each weekly bonus episode of Comfort Zone, Matt, Nil&eacute;ane, and Chris invite listeners to join them in the Cozy Zone, where they&rsquo;ll cover extra topics, invent wilder challenges and games, and share all their great (and not-so-great) takes on tech. The show is an excellent way to get to know the hosts better and participate in the fun you already enjoy on Comfort Zone. Here&rsquo;s the trailer.</p>
<div class="media-wrapper" id="div16"><iframe loading="lazy" title="Welcome to Cozy Zone (It&rsquo;s Comfort Zone, but Cozier.)" width="768" height="432" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/nE-3QSO98TM?feature=oembed" frameborder="0" allow="accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share" referrerpolicy="strict-origin-when-cross-origin" allowfullscreen></iframe></div>
<p id="p17">The first episode of Cozy Zone is being released publicly so everyone can get a taste of it right now. You&rsquo;ll find it today in the <a href="https://feeds.libsyn.com/531557/rss" rel="noopener noreferrer">Comfort Zone feed</a> and on <a href="https://www.youtube.com/playlist?list=PLDSpdP6G2mHuQfDP4-fM8XQxLYmc90xNi" rel="noopener noreferrer">YouTube</a>. Going forward, Cozy Zone will be audio-only for now, but if we hear from enough listeners who want it, we&rsquo;ll work on making video versions a regular option, too. The first episode is available to watch here:</p>
<div class="media-wrapper" id="div18"><iframe loading="lazy" title="Cozy Zone, Episode 1: Defend Your Desk (Bonus Episode)" width="768" height="432" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/cmiKtHCCX4U?feature=oembed" frameborder="0" allow="accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share" referrerpolicy="strict-origin-when-cross-origin" allowfullscreen></iframe></div>
<p id="p19">Episode 1 of Cozy Zone is available in the Comfort Zone audio-only podcast feeds too.</p>
<p id="p20">You can get cozy with the Comfort Zone crew for just <a href="https://macstories.memberful.com/checkout?plan=138191" rel="noopener noreferrer">$5/month</a> or <a href="https://macstories.memberful.com/checkout?plan=138195" rel="noopener noreferrer">$50/year</a>, which not only makes the bonus episodes possible, but supports Comfort Zone, too. The gang has already recorded the first few episodes, and they&rsquo;re great. We think you&rsquo;ll love them as well. To keep up with Cozy Zone, be sure to follow the existing Comfort Zone accounts on <a href="https://mastodon.macstories.net/@comfortzone" rel="noopener noreferrer">Mastodon</a> and <a href="https://bsky.app/profile/comfortzone.macstories.net" rel="noopener noreferrer">Bluesky</a>.</p>
<p id="p21">Finally, thanks to everyone who reads MacStories and listens to our shows. It means a lot to us. We have no shortage of ideas of ways we can make MacStories even better than it was yesterday or is today, but without you all reading, listening, and spreading the word about what we do to your friends and family, it wouldn&rsquo;t be possible. The MacStories community is strong and the kind of foundation that has allowed us to weather fundamental shifts in the online media world. Thank you for all you&rsquo;ve done and continue to do for MacStories.</p>
